gurmukhi: ਬਾਹੈ ਕ੍ਰਿਪਾਣ ਨਿਸੰਗ ॥ ਮਚਯੋ ਅਪੂਰਬ ਜੰਗ ॥੨੨॥
transliteration: Baahai Kridaan Nisan|| Machyo Apoorab Jan||22||
translation: They are striking their swords without any suspicion and in this way, a unique war is going on.22.

gurmukhi: ਬਾਹ ਕ੍ਰਿਪਾਣ ਸੁਬਾਣ ਭੱਟ ਗਣ ॥ ਅੰਤਿ ਗਿਰੇ ਪੁਨਿ ਜੂਝ ਮਹਾਂ ਰਣ ॥
transliteration: Baah Kridaan Soubaan Bhatt Gad|| Ant(i) Gire Poun(i) Joojh Mahaan Ran||
translation: After striking their swords and arrows, the brave fighters ultimately fell down during that great war.

gurmukhi: ਘਾੲਿ ਲਗੈ ੲਿਮ ਘਾੲਿਲ ਝੂਲੈ ॥ ਫਾਗਨਿ ਅੰਤਿ ਬਸੰਤ ਸਫੂਲੈ ॥੨੩॥
transliteration: Ghaae Lagad Im Ghaail Jhdolai|| Phaagad(i) Ant(i) Basant Saphdolai||23||
translation: The wounded warriors are swinging like the blossomed spring at the end of the month of Phagun.23.

gurmukhi: ਬਾਹਿ ਕਟੀ ਭਟ ੲੇਕਨ ਅੈਸੀ ॥ ਸੁੰਡ ਮਨੋ ਗਜ ਰਾਜਨ ਜੈਸੀ ॥
transliteration: Baah(i) Katibhat Ekan Aisee|| Sound Mano Gad Raajan Jaisee||
translation: Somewhere the chopped arms of the warriors appear like the trunks of the elephants;

gurmukhi: ਸੋਹਤ ੲੇਕ ਅਨੇਕ ਪ੍ਰਕਾਰੰ ॥ ਫੂਲ ਖਿਰੇ ਜਮੁ ਮੱਧਿ ਫੁਲਵਾਰੰ ॥੨੪॥
transliteration: Shoat Ek Anek Prakaaran|| Phool Khire Jam(u) Madhh(i) Phulvaaran||24||
translation: The brave fighters appear beautiful like the flowers blooming in the garden.24.

gurmukhi: ਸ੍ਰੋਣ ਰੰਗੇ ਅਰ ੲੇਕ ਅਨੇਕੰ ॥ ਫੂਲ ਰਹੇ ਜਨੁ ਕਿੰਸੁਕ ਨੇਕੰ ॥
transliteration: Sron Rane Ar Ek Anekan|| Phool Rahe Jan(u) Kinsouk Nekan||
translation: The enemies were dyed with blood like many types of blooming flowers.

gurmukhi: ਧਾਵਤ ਘਾਵ ਕ੍ਰਿਪਾਣ ਪ੍ਹਾਰੰ ॥ ਜਾਨਕ ਕੋਪੁ ਪ੍ਰਤੱਛ ਦਿਖਾਰੰ ॥੨੫॥
transliteration: Dhaavat Ghaav Kridaan Prahaaran|| Jaanak Kop(u) Pratachchh Dikhaaran||25||
translation: After having been wounded with swords the brave soldiers were roaming like the manifestation of anger itself.25.

gurmukhi: ਜੂਝ ਗਿਰੇ ਅਰ ੲੇਕ ਅਨੇਕੰ ॥ ਘਾੲਿ ਲਗੈ ਬਿਸੰਭਾਰ ਬਿਸੇਖੰ ॥
transliteration: Joojh Gire Ar Ek Anekan|| Ghaae Lagad Bisanbhaar Bisekhan||
translation: Many enemies fell down fighting and Narsingh, the incarnation of Vishnu also received many wounds.

gurmukhi: ਕਾਟਿ ਗਿਰੇ ਭਟ ੲੇਕਹ ਵਾਰੰ ॥ ਸਾਬਨ ਜਾਨ ਗੲੀ ਬਹ ਤਾਰੰ ॥੨੬॥
transliteration: Kaattee Gire Bhat Ekah Vaaran|| Saabah Jaan Gadi Bah Taaran||26||
translation: The chopped bits of the warriors were flowing in the stream of blood like the bubbles of foam.26.
